1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,771
Now combine the method into one Decision-Ready Research Brief.

2
00:00:03,721 --> 00:00:06,096
The brief is not a magic prompt.

3
00:00:06,096 --> 00:00:13,317
It is a compact contract that lets the researcher plan, gather, evaluate, and deliver work against visible expectations.

4
00:00:13,317 --> 00:00:19,000
Field one is decision and audience: who will use the work, what they must decide, and by when.

5
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:26,964
Field two is question and scope: the main question, region, timeframe, population, comparison set, and exclusions.

6
00:00:26,964 --> 00:00:34,339
Field three is research plan and source strategy: the sub-questions, priority source types, and evaluation criteria.

7
00:00:34,339 --> 00:00:42,125
Field four is evidence standard: which claims need citations, how source quality should be recorded, and how conflicts should be handled.

8
00:00:42,125 --> 00:00:50,134
Field five is gaps and confidence: required unknowns, stop conditions, limitations, and what evidence could change the conclusion.

9
00:00:50,134 --> 00:01:00,627
Field six is deliverable and next action: format, required sections, length, audience, recommendation, evidence appendix, and the decision or follow-up that comes next.

10
00:01:00,627 --> 00:01:05,298
After the first report, use targeted follow-ups instead of restarting vaguely.

11
00:01:05,298 --> 00:01:07,903
Go deeper on the decisive uncertainty.

12
00:01:07,903 --> 00:01:11,173
Validate a contested claim with stronger sources.

13
00:01:11,173 --> 00:01:14,192
Compare two options under the same criteria.

14
00:01:14,192 --> 00:01:17,961
Update the brief when the scope or acceptance standard changes.

15
00:01:17,961 --> 00:01:23,480
The common failure is writing a ceremonial prompt full of context that cannot affect the research.

16
00:01:23,480 --> 00:01:28,692
Every field should change the plan, the evidence, the evaluation, or the deliverable.

17
00:01:28,692 --> 00:01:31,759
If a sentence changes none of those, remove it.

18
00:01:31,759 --> 00:01:38,009
First, package decision, scope, plan, evidence, gaps, and delivery in one brief.

19
00:01:38,009 --> 00:01:42,461
Second, make every field change how the research is performed or reviewed.

20
00:01:42,461 --> 00:01:47,480
Third, iterate by deepening, validating, or comparing the decisive uncertainty.
